== Current use
FreeMoCap has been used in a number of research studies already. A recent study by Mazrouei et al. utilized FreeMoCap when examining kinematics of reaching and grasping in the hand @mazroueiCatchingSmallBalls2026. Núñez-Lisboa et al. found that they were able to use FreeMoCap to detect changes in sagittal-joint mechanics from controlled postural manipulations @nunez-lisboaUnderstandingGaitAlterations2024. Darici et al. found a 3 camera FreeMoCap system could accurately capture spatiotemporal gait parameters and further found that FreeMoCap could be suitable for use in Functional Gait Analysis @dariciLowCostMarkerlessMotion2025a. Minogue et al. found high correlation and low RMSE in measuring squat movement and countermovement jumps against a marker-based system @minogueValidationFreetoUseMarkerless2025. The software has also been mentioned in a series of corpus-building papers in the computational linguistics field @peechattMULTICOLLABMultimodalCorpus2024 @orrMULTICOLLABASLAffectiveComputing2024 @nunnariDGSFabeln1MultiAngleParallel2024.  

While the primary focus of this work is on the potential research and clinical use of this software, it would be wrong not to mention that a great number of FreeMoCap users are animators and game developers. 